caption: Well kept and clean cemetery where I like to go reading and sunbathing. With all the respect towards all buried people of course.
GOOD Includes a small Muslim square but I wonder if the tombs are oriented towards Mecca?

My husband's parents & uncles are buried there, calm & rest are not empty words there, whether for the dead or the living. The paths are very well maintained. The benches, for their part, allow for relaxing meditation. As I no longer live in this area, I unfortunately can no longer go there. Therefore, I thank Monique for the information on the schedules, this will allow me to give them to our daughter who lives in the 13th.

For 30 years I have come every year from the Province, 600kms to put flowers on my husband's grave, I arrive around 12:15 p.m., the very unpleasant curator does not want to open the gate for us, I am disabled, the other years no problem , but there really the new staff to review, unacceptable, All Saints' Day week. I will file a complaint with the Mayor. In addition incorrect opening hours on the Web.

the times on the website are incorrect. the cemetery opens from 9:00 a.m. to 5:00 p.m. including Saturdays with the possibility of entering with the.  car.On Sundays cars are not allowed to enter the cemetery.
It is a small cemetery close to Paris but curiously calm and pleasant. Families maintain the graves regularly. Small benches to sit and meditate
A very beautiful cemetery where you can stroll peacefully. The caretaker is very friendly and at your disposal for any questions (e.g. the location of a grave).
Cemetery very well maintained by a small team of gardeners Garden of soldiers who died during different wars Some tombs may be of people known at their time.

Not very well maintained....plus I go to the cemetery Wednesday May 19, 2020 closing at 12 p.m....and when I look at the times on the internet I see 8 a.m. to 6 p.m....you don't care about people, it's a lack of respect ....
Place of peace to think of our dear dead but poorly maintained compared to Parisian cemeteries
